  see all updates](https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/13/24216322/google-pixel-9-launch-event-live-blog-news-announcements-products)
  
  Google announced a new image generation app during its [Pixel 9 event today](https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/13/24216322/google-pixel-9-launch-event-live-blog-news-announcements-products). The company says the app, called Pixel Studio, will come preinstalled on every [Pixel 9 device](https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/13/24218879/googles-pixel-9-lineup-is-a-pro-show).
  
  Pixel Studio, much like Apple’s forthcoming [Image Playground](https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/10/24175523/apple-ai-custom-emoji-images-ios18-wwdc) app that’s set to roll out on iOS 18 at some point after the operating system launches, lets you create an image from a prompt. Users can edit images after the fact, using the prompt box to add or subtract elements and change the feel or style of the picture.
  
