  # Create images with Pixel Studio
  
  **Important:**
  
  - Pixel Studio is available for these devices, languages, and countries:
    - **Devices:** Pixel 9, Pixel 9 Pro, Pixel 9 Pro XL, Pixel 9 Pro Fold, Pixel 9a, Pixel 10, Pixel 10 Pro, Pixel 10 Pro XL, Pixel 10 Pro Fold
    - **Languages:** English, German, Japanese
    - **Countries:** Australia, Austria, Canada, Germany, India, Ireland, Japan, Malaysia, Singapore, Switzerland, United Kingdom, United States
  - Pixel Studio is not available in the work profile or on a fully managed device.
  
  You can easily create and share unique and fun images with generative AI on Pixel Studio. [Learn more about Google's GenAI policies](https://policies.google.com/terms/generative-ai/use-policy).
  
  ## Use Pixel Studio
  
  ### Create an image
  
  1. Open the Pixel Studio app.
  2. Select a pre-designed layout or tap **Create**.
  3. Describe your image in the text box.
  4. To re-create new versions, tap Regenerate ![](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/la0Pq82KO9PQAkYq8bQWi7ZiGhXAZYVIMsta).
  5. To explore different styles, tap Styles ![](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/LkxID3nSPVRW7MXGMvtsFKWHqThN0QkuB5sD).
  
  ### Return to a project
  
  1. Open the Pixel Studio app.
  2. From the home page, at the top left, tap My Projects ![](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/YtehqvFHgz7Anxmnazk2rzocNF2NCnMARmXk).
  3. Tap the image you want to edit.
     - If it’s an image you created, you can change the prompt, add stickers, change the style of the image, add captions or remove objects.
  
  ### Edit your photos
  
  1. Open the Pixel Studio app.
  2. From the home page, at the bottom, tap the image icon and select a photo from your camera roll.
  3. Tap **Edit image**.
  4. Select a tool:
     - To adjust your image borders, tap Crop ![Crop](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/5Ta5tW8o1Ltd0nDWKBX0p81nS5ijKb8t0cCn).
     - To doodle, highlight, or add something to your image, tap Draw ![Draw](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/TxjFbK7wu8dXlO9Ap5D6y5rGRjXgCq3Bi9vG).
     - To add a text, tap Label ![Label](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/5pvPxQNMdUFxF3os01aIEgH5kTqYLsHLu4Bk).
     - To add a new creation, tap Insert ![Wand](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/gLN2cFcXhD4yMvkE0LIAPrRV46sAeO8zhjVF).
     - To add or create a sticker, tap Sticker ![Sticker](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/Vv5Wjb56JuQixk4QXNNHMrXJxM2H0SUu3Zl0).
     - To remove a section in the image, tap Erase ![Erase](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/JF5goq5fFkcjsgy5gCu3IF9GJQQ3u8JkXvUV).
  
       **Tip:** To undo changes, tap Undo ![](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/DkzReBcE8uLYy9lDHXeAVOfqSmDbiSyTMTzc).
  5. Tap **Save**.
  
  ### Add or replace objects with AI
  
  1. Open the Pixel Studio app.
  2. From the home page:
     - To select a photo from your camera roll, tap **Image**.
     - To make a new image, tap **Create**.
  3. Tap Insert ![Wand](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/gLN2cFcXhD4yMvkE0LIAPrRV46sAeO8zhjVF).
  
     - Use Quick Select or Manual Select to select an area and describe what you want to add or replace.
     - Then Circle, tap, or brush the part that you want to edit.
     - Use Expand to expand your selected area. Use Deselect to remove parts of your selected area.
  4. Describe and enter a prompt like: Add `a baseball cap` or `Insert a sun`.
  5. Tap **Enter**.
  
  - To add the image, tap Accept ![Accept](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/b0rQfmSEFoISNMWYxIkWy3wu0IIWOG5J1pW7).
  
  
    - If you don’t like the result and want Pixel Studio to try again, tap Reload ![Reload](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/Q4DSSf07Sx2KZglBSgmKipnCdBHI7tborMlA).
    - To remove the object, tap Undo ![](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/DkzReBcE8uLYy9lDHXeAVOfqSmDbiSyTMTzc).
  
  ### Create & save a sticker to Gboard
  
  To liven up a message, you can create a sticker, save it to your Google Keyboard (Gboard), and send it to friends and family.
  
  With this feature you can:
  
  - Send Pixel Studio stickers in any messaging app with Gboard.
  - Create new stickers in the "My projects" library with the "Stickers" tab or from your sticker library while you edit a creation.
  
  1. Open the Pixel Studio app.
  2. At the bottom, tap the **Sticker** icon.
  3. Under "Create a sticker," tap **Describe your sticker** or **Make one from existing photo**.
  
  From your My projects library:
  
  1. Open the Pixel Studio app.
  2. At the top left, tap the **My projects**![and then](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3_l97rr0GvhSP2XV5OoCkV2ZDTIisAOczrSdzNCBxhIKWrjXjHucxNwocghoUa39gw=h36) **Stickers**.
  3. Follow the on-screen instructions to create a sticker.
  
  Send the sticker:
  
  1. In your messaging app, open Gboard ![Gboard](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-NDjyE1oA_AD7nyidEBUsJVVurifsnAl7ohTmHxS0mybbND2DkfZsfXUkaHBkjIwkNM=w36-h36).
  2. Tap **Stickers**![and then](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3_l97rr0GvhSP2XV5OoCkV2ZDTIisAOczrSdzNCBxhIKWrjXjHucxNwocghoUa39gw=h36) **Pixel Studio**.
  3. Select a sticker to send.
  
  ## Download images from Pixel Studio
  
  ### Save images from Pixel Studio
  
  **Important:** You can’t save stickers.
  
  1. Open the Pixel Studio app.
  2. On the home page, at the top left, tap My Projects ![](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/YtehqvFHgz7Anxmnazk2rzocNF2NCnMARmXk).
  3. Tap the image you want to download.
  4. To save the image to your device, tap Download ![](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/mxhT8m6z_VLm48Nn8xv0lEE0hsXdLpNihNgbRc2-mWgdWAxmtRCSgSik6FyrTqKGSw=h36).
  
  ### View your saved images in Google Photos
  
  1. Open the Google Photos app ![Photos](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/FCkTSCEsNJWvoPb9QjjUwoQ9m0x1grNbkXgN)
  2. At the bottom, tap Collections ![](https://storage.googleapis.com/support-kms-prod/q7so83p5wQOzOvsh7zzmIRfczad4D9jnItnO)![and then](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3_l97rr0GvhSP2XV5OoCkV2ZDTIisAOczrSdzNCBxhIKWrjXjHucxNwocghoUa39gw=h36)**On this device**.
  3. To view your saved images, tap **Pixel Studio**.
  
  ## Image restrictions
  
  You won’t be able to generate any images that violate [Google’s Generative AI Prohibited Use Policy](https://policies.google.com/terms/generative-ai). Note that some images may be unintentionally blocked as we fine-tune our filters.
  
